==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Cubeb
<hw>Cu"beb</hw> <pr>(k⟦umac⟧"b⟦ecr⟧b)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>cub⟦egrave⟧be</ets> (cf. It. <ets>cubebe</ets>, Pr., Sp., Pg., &
NL. <ets>cubeba</ets>), fr. Ar. <ets>kab⟦amac⟧bat</ets>.]</ety> <def>The
small, spicy berry of a species of pepper (<spn>Piper Cubeba</spn>; in
<fld>(Med.)</fld>, <spn>Cubeba officinalis</spn>), native in Java and
Borneo, but now cultivated in various tropical countries. The dried
unripe fruit is much used in medicine as a stimulant and
purgative.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>cubebic</ent>⟦br⟧
